entries.femaleVariant: Fuck! Panam!
So it begins.
What's the meaning of this?
Exactly what you see. The Basilisk.
Do you want to serve corporations forever? Fine, go right ahead.
In that case, we'll leave the Basilisk as a souvenir of what this family used to be.
All I see is two trucks with giant Militech logos on them.
As soon as I'm done with Biotechnica, we call a family meeting to discuss this, discuss you.
Bob, Mitch – you two take the trucks around back.
And the Basilisk? Can we put it together?
Seems like the family's on your side.
Everything all right?
Everything OK?
And... V? You shouldn't have spoken.
I know. It's just… he pissed me off.
Yes, of course. Though the great train robbery bit of this was much more enjoyable.
We need to unload.
Sure, but then what do we do with them?
The Raffens could rear their heads at any moment.
Or, you know what? Maybe next time we're attacked, we'll be able to fight back!
Fuck! Panam, you can see them from miles away!
And now we have Militech to worry about, too!
STOP IT! FUCK! Just shut up already!
Until that time, I want these trucks out of my sight.
You think we don't have problems enough on our hands?
Got quite a pair o' lungs, there.
Thanks. I believe the last time I pulled something like that, I was ten years old.
Seem still to be in fine working order.
You're telling me.
Do what you want. Just get out of my sight.
Family's with you on this, I think.
Sure... Where did you get that impression? All I heard was silence.
Saw 'em lookin' at that Basilisk, drooling.
entries.maleVariant: Saw them lookin' at that Basilisk, drooling.

entries.femaleVariant: Nomads – panzers. Panzers – nomads. Had 'em from the start.
We'll see.
I am sure I will. So you'd better expect that call.
You need me again, all you gotta do is call.
Be waiting. Take care.
Oh, I've got an idea.
You need me again, let me know.
Some lungs you got.
